        <img height="15" alt="" src="/print/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif"/><br />

<a name="3362"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Tweet, Poke and Link to Stay Connected to CES</div>
<br />
No surprise, a consumer technology tradeshow is leading by example when it comes to using Internet technology to stay connected. Pick your social media tool of choice to get late-breaking news about CES, including major press announcements, keynote additions, exhibitor news and more.<BR><BR><A href="http://www.cesweb.org/twitter" target=_blank><STRONG>CES on: Twitter</STRONG><BR><IMG border=0 hspace=6 align=right src="/print/images/content/twitter.png" width=88 height=21></A>CES followers and fanatics use Twitter to post links to blogs and articles well after the show doors have closed. Get story ideas and connect through this popular social media tool with the tag #CES.&nbsp;&nbsp; <BR><BR><A href="http://www.cesweb.org/facebook" target=_blank><STRONG>CES on: Facebook</STRONG></A><BR><A href="http://www.cesweb.org/facebook" target=_blank><IMG border=0 hspace=6 align=right src="/print/images/content/facebook_sm.jpg" width=85 height=32></A>Check out the International CES Page on Facebook. Become a fan to connect with other professionals that share your interests and stay informed on the 2010 International CES. Facebook is a registered trademark of Facebook, Inc. <BR><BR><A href="http://www.cesweb.org/linkedin" target=_blank><STRONG>CES on: LinkedIn</STRONG><BR><IMG border=0 hspace=6 align=right src="/print/images/content/linked_in.png" width=96 height=28></A>One of the Internet's first networking sites is a great resource for CES attendees and the consumer technology industry in general.<BR><BR><A href="http://www.cesweb.org/youtube" target=_blank><STRONG>CES on: YouTube</STRONG></A><BR><A href="http://www.cesweb.org/youtube" target=_blank><IMG border=0 hspace=6 align=right src="/print/images/content/youtube.png" width=88 height=36></A>Tune in to YouTube to see highlights from the 2009 CES. As we draw closer to the 2010 show, you'll see more videos emerge about consumer technology trends and other buzz that's building from the mere thought of the doors opening at the world's largest consumer technology tradeshow.

